  "reasoning": "The original implementation cached product dictionaries but did not keep the cache in sync when a product was updated. update_product updated only the backing _db, leaving the _cache entry stale; get_product then continued to return outdated data. I fixed this by ensuring any change to the product data also updates (or invalidates and repopulates) the cache. I also made the caching semantics clearer and safer: get_product now always returns a shallow copy of the product data to prevent callers from mutating cached objects directly, and add_product populates the cache so subsequent reads are fast and consistent. I kept the module-level API identical (add_product, get_product, update_product, reset) but improved docstrings, added type hints, and clarified behavior in comments.",
